🚨 2. Content View & Lifecycle Promotion
          In Satellite, patches are never directly applied to production.

          🔁 Goal: Move a patch safely:
                        👉  Library → Dev → Test → UAT → Prod
              Publish a New Version:
                              Path: 
                                  👉 Content → Content Views → [Your CV] → Publish New Version
                              This creates:
                                    Version 1.0 → old
                                    Version 2.0 → new (with patches)

          🚀 Promote Through Lifecycle
                        Path:
                        Content → Content Views → Versions → Promote
                        Promote step-by-step:
                        🔁 Promotion Flow:
                                    Library → Dev
                                    Dev → Test
                                    Test → UAT
                                    UAT → Prod

🔄 3. Register Client (If Starting Fresh)
         ⚙️ Step-by-Step: Generate Activation Key (dev_key)
            🔑 Step 1: Go to Activation Keys
                        In Satellite UI:
                              👉 Content → Activation Keys
            ➕ Step 2: Create New Key
                        Click:
                              👉 Create Activation Key
                              ✔   Fill details:
                                          Basic Info:
                                              *  Name: dev_key
                                              *  Description: Dev environment key
                                              *  Environment: Dev
                                              *  Content View: Your CV (e.g., RHEL_CV)
                                              *  Limit: (optional, leave blank for unlimited)

            Note:-New Dev servers provisioned OR existing servers not yet registered
                  You need to onboard all servers to Red Hat Satellite
                  👉 You do NOT log into each server.
                  👉 You use automation from a control node using Ansible

                  🖥️ 🧩 Architecture (Real Setup)

                        [ Ansible Control Node ]
                                  |
                                  | SSH
                                  ↓
                        [ Dev Server 1 ]
                        [ Dev Server 2 ]
                        [ Dev Server 3 ]
                        ...
                        [ Dev Server 100 ]
                                  |
                                  ↓
                             [ Satellite ]

                  📂 1. Inventory File (Dev Servers)
                  example:-
                        Create file: inventory.ini
                                      [dev]
                                      dev-app-01
                                      dev-app-02
                                      dev-db-01
                                      dev-web-01

                     Note:   👉 In real env: could be 100+ servers

                   ⚙️ 2. REAL-TIME PLAYBOOK (Production Ready)
                      Create file: register_dev.yml

                        - name: Register all Dev servers to Satellite
                          hosts: dev
                          become: yes
                          gather_facts: no
                        
                          vars:
                            satellite_url: "http://satellite.example.com"
                            org: "Your_Org"
                            activation_key: "dev_key"
                        
                          tasks:
                        
                            - name: Install Katello CA consumer package
                              yum:
                                name: "{{ satellite_url }}/pub/katello-ca-consumer-latest.noarch.rpm"
                                state: present
                                disable_gpg_check: yes
                        
                            - name: Ensure system is not already registered
                              command: subscription-manager status
                              register: reg_status
                              ignore_errors: yes
                        
                            - name: Register system to Satellite
                              command: >
                                subscription-manager register
                                --org="{{ org }}"
                                --activationkey="{{ activation_key }}"
                              when: reg_status.rc != 0
                        
                            - name: Refresh subscription
                              command: subscription-manager refresh
                        
                            - name: Verify repos
                              command: yum repolist
                              register: repo_output
                        
                            - name: Show repo output
                              debug:
                                var: repo_output.stdout_lines

                  ▶️ 3. Execute Playbook From control node:
                              ansible-playbook -i inventory.ini register_dev.yml

                  ⚡ What Happens
                        In a few seconds/minutes:
                              All 100 servers:
                                    Install Katello CA
                                    Register to Satellite
                                    Attach Dev environment
                                    Get Content View

                  🧪 4. REAL-TIME VALIDATION
                        ✅ On any Dev server execute the below commands:
                                   👉 subscription-manager identity
                                   👉 yum repolist

                        ✅ In Satellite UI:
                              Go to: Hosts → Content Hosts
                              👉 You’ll see all Dev servers listed

Note:- 
🧭 What is this package:-  rpm -Uvh http://satellite-server/pub/katello-ca-consumer-latest.noarch.rpm
  This installs the Katello CA Consumer package from your **Red Hat Satellite server.
   🎯 What does it actually do?
            When installed on a client (RHEL server), it performs 3 critical functions:
            🔐 1. Installs SSL Certificates (Trust)
                  Adds Satellite’s CA certificate to the system
                  Ensures secure HTTPS communication
                  👉 Without this:
                        Registration fails
                        SSL errors occur
            🌐 2. Configures Subscription Manager
                  It updates: /etc/rhsm/rhsm.conf
                  👉 Changes: Default CDN → Satellite server
                              So instead of:  cdn.redhat.com
                              It points to: satellite.example.com
            📦 3. Enables Satellite-Based Repositories
                        Redirects all yum/dnf traffic to Satellite
                        Ensures:
                            *  Controlled patching
                            *  No internet dependency

🔍 How to verify it worked After installing execute the command:  cat /etc/rhsm/rhsm.conf | grep hostname
                                                                              (or)
                                                                   rpm -qa | grep katello-ca
  👉 Should show your Satellite server
  👉 The katello-ca-consumer package is connects your client system to Satellite securely and correctly Without it,
      Satellite management will not work properly.
🔁 When do you install it?
      ✅ You install it ONLY when:
           * A system is being registered for the first time
           * A system is newly built (new VM / server)
           * A system was previously connected to CDN and now moved to Satellite
